      "instruction": "In a small bowl, combine all spices for the cajun seasoning and mix together. Set aside. Store any extra in an airtight container for future use."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "In a heavy bottom pot (such as a Dutch oven), heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil over medium heat."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Add the sliced chicken and 2\u00bd tablespoons of the prepared cajun seasoning."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Add the andouille sausage and cook until the chicken is no longer pink, about 4-5 minutes."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Remove the meat from the pot and add the remaining olive oil."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Add the diced peppers and onions and cook until the onions are transparent and softened, about 5 minutes."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Add the milk and stir so that the seasoning is incorporated into the liquid."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Turn the heat to high and bring to a boil."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Add the uncooked fettuccine, stirring constantly until the noodles are al dente, about 10 minutes."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "On low heat, add the meat back in and stir so that it\u2019s evenly incorporated."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Add the cheese and parsley, and stir. Remove from the heat."
    }
